**SSR (Server-Side Rendering)** — Renders on every request

```tsx
export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic';

async function getData() {
  const res = await fetch(url, { cache: 'no-store' });
  return res.json();
}

export default async function Page() {
  const data = await getData();  // Fresh on every request
  return <div>{data.content}</div>;
}
```

**How it works:**
1. User requests page
2. Server fetches fresh data
3. Server renders HTML
4. Browser receives updated HTML

**When to use:**
✅ Personalized content (user dashboards)
✅ Real-time data (stock prices, live scores)
✅ Frequently changing data (news feeds)
✅ Authentication-dependent pages

---

**SSG (Static Site Generation)** — Pre-renders at build time

```tsx
async function getData() {
  const res = await fetch(url);  // Default: cached forever
  return res.json();
}

export default async function Page() {
  const data = await getData();  // Fetched once at build
  return <div>{data.content}</div>;
}
```

**How it works:**
1. At build time, server fetches data
2. Server generates HTML files
3. Every request serves the same HTML (super fast!)

**When to use:**
✅ Static content (about, FAQ, landing pages)
✅ Blog posts (content rarely changes)
✅ Documentation
✅ Marketing pages

---

**ISR (Incremental Static Regeneration)** — Static + periodic updates

```tsx
async function getData() {
  const res = await fetch(url, {
    next: { revalidate: 3600 }  // Revalidate every hour
  });
  return res.json();
}

export default async function Page() {
  const data = await getData();
  return <div>{data.content}</div>;
}
```

**How it works:**
1. First request generates static HTML
2. Serves cached HTML (fast!)
3. After revalidation time, regenerates in background
4. Subsequent requests get updated HTML

**When to use:**
✅ E-commerce (product inventory updates)
✅ Blog (new posts added periodically)
✅ News sites (articles published hourly)
✅ Any content that updates on a schedule

---

**Summary:**

| Strategy | When to Use | Performance | Freshness |
|----------|-------------|-------------|------------|
| SSG | Static content | ⚡⚡⚡ Fastest | Stale until rebuild |
| ISR | Periodic updates | ⚡⚡ Fast | Fresh after revalidation |
| SSR | Real-time/personalized | ⚡ Slower | Always fresh |

**Server Components can fetch data directly** using async/await:

**1. Default (cached forever - SSG):**

```tsx
async function getData() {
  // ✅ Default: Cached indefinitely
  const res = await fetch('https://api.example.com/data');
  return res.json();
}

export default async function Page() {
  const data = await getData();
  return <div>{data.title}</div>;
}
```

**When:** Static content that never changes

---

**2. No cache (always fresh - SSR):**

```tsx
async function getData() {
  // ❌ Never cached - always fetches fresh
  const res = await fetch('https://api.example.com/data', {
    cache: 'no-store'
  });
  return res.json();
}

export default async function Page() {
  const data = await getData();  // Fresh on every request
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>{data.title}</h1>
      <p>Generated at: {new Date().toLocaleTimeString()}</p>
    </div>
  );
}
```

**When:** Real-time data, user-specific content

---

**3. Time-based revalidation (ISR):**

```tsx
async function getData() {
  // ⏱️ Cached, revalidates every 60 seconds
  const res = await fetch('https://api.example.com/data', {
    next: { revalidate: 60 }
  });
  return res.json();
}

export default async function Page() {
  const data = await getData();
  return <div>{data.title}</div>;
}
```

**When:** Content updates periodically

---

**4. Tag-based revalidation (on-demand ISR):**

```tsx
async function getData() {
  // 🏷️ Tagged for on-demand revalidation
  const res = await fetch('https://api.example.com/data', {
    next: { 
      revalidate: 3600,  // Also revalidate every hour
      tags: ['homepage', 'featured']
    }
  });
  return res.json();
}

export default async function Page() {
  const data = await getData();
  return <div>{data.title}</div>;
}
```

Trigger revalidation:
```tsx
// app/api/revalidate/route.ts
import { revalidateTag } from 'next/cache';

export async function POST() {
  revalidateTag('homepage');  // Revalidate all fetches with this tag
  return Response.json({ revalidated: true });
}
```

**When:** Event-driven updates (CMS webhooks, admin updates)

