**Environment variables** store configuration and secrets outside your code.

**Two types in Next.js:**

1. **Server-only** (no prefix) — Only accessible on server
2. **Public** (`NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix) — Accessible everywhere

---

**Setup:**

```bash
# .env.local (not committed to Git)

# ❌ PRIVATE - Server only
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@localhost/db
API_SECRET_KEY=super-secret-key-12345
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_...

# ✅ PUBLIC - Browser accessible
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.example.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_NAME=My Awesome Site
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_ANALYTICS=UA-12345678
```

---

**Server Components (all variables accessible):**

```tsx
// app/products/page.tsx (Server Component)

async function getProducts() {
  // ✅ Can access private variables
  const res = await fetch(`${process.env.API_URL}/products`, {
    headers: {
      'Authorization': `Bearer ${process.env.API_SECRET_KEY}`
    }
  });
  return res.json();
}

export default async function ProductsPage() {
  const products = await getProducts();

  // ✅ Can access public variables
  const siteName = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_NAME;

  return (
    <div>
      <h1>{siteName} - Products</h1>
      {products.map(product => (
        <div key={product.id}>{product.name}</div>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}
```

---

**Client Components (only NEXT_PUBLIC_ accessible):**

```tsx
// app/components/Analytics.js
'use client';

export default function Analytics() {
  // ✅ Public variable works
  const analyticsId = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_ANALYTICS;
  console.log('Analytics ID:', analyticsId);  // ✅ Works

  // ❌ Private variable is undefined in browser
  const secretKey = process.env.API_SECRET_KEY;
  console.log('Secret:', secretKey);  // undefined

  return <div>Analytics initialized</div>;
}
```

---

**API Routes (all variables accessible):**

```tsx
// app/api/users/route.ts

export async function GET() {
  // ✅ Full access to all environment variables
  const res = await fetch(`${process.env.API_URL}/users`, {
    headers: {
      'Authorization': `Bearer ${process.env.API_SECRET_KEY}`
    }
  });

  const users = await res.json();
  return Response.json(users);
}
```

---

**Security Table:**

| Variable Type | Example | Server Component | Client Component | API Route |
|--------------|---------|------------------|------------------|----------|
| Private | `DATABASE_URL` | ✅ Yes | ❌ undefined | ✅ Yes |
| Private | `API_SECRET_KEY` | ✅ Yes | ❌ undefined | ✅ Yes |
| Public | `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` | ✅ Yes | ✅ Yes | ✅ Yes |
| Public | `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_NAME` | ✅ Yes | ✅ Yes | ✅ Yes |

---

**⚠️ DANGER: Don't expose secrets!**

```tsx
// ❌ DANGEROUS - Secret exposed to browser!
'use client';

export default function BadComponent() {
  // This WON'T work but shows intent to expose secret
  const secret = process.env.API_SECRET_KEY;  // undefined
  return <div>{secret}</div>;
}

// ❌ DANGEROUS - Accidentally making secret public
// .env.local
NEXT_PUBLIC_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://...  // ❌ NEVER DO THIS!
```

---

**✅ Best Practices:**

```tsx
// 1. Validate environment variables on startup
// lib/env.js

function getEnvVar(key) {
  const value = process.env[key];
  if (!value) {
    throw new Error(`Missing environment variable: ${key}`);
  }
  return value;
}

export const env = {
  // Private (server-only)
  databaseUrl: getEnvVar('DATABASE_URL'),
  apiSecretKey: getEnvVar('API_SECRET_KEY'),

  // Public (browser-safe)
  apiUrl: getEnvVar('NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL'),
  siteName: getEnvVar('NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_NAME'),
};
```

```tsx
// 2. Use in components
import { env } from '@/lib/env';

export default async function Page() {
  const res = await fetch(`${env.apiUrl}/data`, {
    headers: {
      'Authorization': `Bearer ${env.apiSecretKey}`
    }
  });
  // ...
}
```

```tsx
